      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 128: 🔴 Critical Issues - `pluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"]` is applied unconditionally to the displayed message body. If plugin data is provided by plugins or remote-derived message metadata, this lets opaque plugin state silently replace the canonical message text, creating spoofing and auditability risks. The UI should either clearly distinguish plugin-rendered content from message content, or only apply overwrite data produced by a trusted/local plugin handler with explicit validation.\n```suggestion\nif (isTrustedPluginBodyOverwrite(msg.pluginData) \u0026\u0026 !bodyOverwriteIt.value().isEmpty())\n    body \u003d bodyOverwriteIt.value();\n```\nThe concrete helper should validate the source/key according to the daemon plugin-data contract rather than trusting any `bodyOverwrite` key.",
      "revId": "f4231ab9e19439347be689c6c05f3646f406a803",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
