      "message": "[Critical] Line 528: 🔴 Critical Issues - `OriginalBody` falls back to `item.second.body` when the commit body is empty. Since `item.second.body` may already contain the plugin-overwritten body, editing a message with an intentionally empty or missing canonical body can prefill and resend plugin-generated display text instead of the original message. Preserve the distinction by returning the canonical commit value directly when the key exists, even if it is empty.\n```suggestion\ncase Role::OriginalBody: {\n    return QVariant(item.second.commit.contains(\"body\") ? item.second.commit.value(\"body\") : QString {});\n}\n```",
